Alright, so next time... Wait, why am I small? Was there seriously a power up filter in that exit pipe?
BTW, with these power ups being here in this TSA, yeah, there was absolutely no need for the game to filter out my capes when I reached the Green Switch room.
Zwee! Okay, let's quickly enter this pipe while I'm caped...

Whoa. Okay, I see what I need to do here.
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Alright, let's go straight to the voting results here...
Aha! Oh, and now we've got this wall springboard glitch being put to use.
Capeless divebomb FTW! Of course, that filter didn't touch my reserve cape, so I'll just grab that now.
BTW, as far as I can tell, even with block cloning, there doesn't seem to be a way to smuggle Yoshi into Rumia's Fortress (Hard). Oh, well.
"You might have already noticed, but a bunch of the Hard stages have a Scarlet-Devil-style crimson moon in the background. Ah, the oppressive, sepia-toned memories... Ah, the days of my youth..."
Too bad I broke my star-kill combo, or I could've gotten a 2-up from that Wiggler.
Unfortunately, one of the remaining sound channels still plays notes. Oh, well. Anyway, looks like I can be a bit clever with these power up filters.

In the first half, you'll transform as such: Small - Fire - Cape - Small and Star - Small... Except while invincible, if you take damage, you're done for. In the latter half, it'll be all about abusing the cape.

Uh, oh! Run forward, quickly!
Huh, the game made me automatically move south there. I think I just "cleared" a level that wasn't meant to be "cleared". I hope that doesn't screw something up later.

"You're no ordinary guy to make it all the way here, huh? Lunatic World isn't elementary kid play, it's difficult stuff. You're gonna die! You're gonna die HARD! Oh yeah, and Yoshi can't go through these pipes."

...Oh, no... Did I forget to speed up the footage this time? ...Well, whatever. I'm not remaking the video now.
Huh, no lag at all during the green ! block distribution there. Maybe finally getting off my butt and changing "per2exec" in zsnesw.cfg to 150 is actually helping.

Anyway, I unlocked this Top Secret Area, so let's check it out.
HARRY UP!
Go, my green ! blocks, and fill the world with your greenness!

Okay, let's hopefully not die to something else right now. I do not want to have to struggle with that evil turn block wall again!

I don't see why there's a need to restrict Yoshi from leaving here...
I can Start+Select out to avoid your dumb filters here! Take that, game!
Oh, what? I hadn't even changed to small+star yet (since I'm not flashing) when I got crush-killed there! What gives? Anyway, time for quadruple ludicrous speed!
Aw, nuts... Welp, I'm boned.
Whoa, careful. I'm lucky I didn't get crush-killed there.
Well, you know what? Nuts to you!

So, it looks like I'm meant to cape fly here. BTW, the sound channels are no longer disabled now, since this music won't last long enough from this point to be an issue.

Okay, we're revving up the engine to the maximum possible setting-- ludicrous speed squared!!!

So, I went back and checked those comments, and that person is Minori from the anime Toradora.
Now, this part of the level stops with the continuous power up changing mechanic. And thus, the music won't change for a while, so I disabled the sound channels here.
Alright, I'm going to double the speed of the footage for a moment until I get back there.

Oh, if I can avoid stomping or grabbing anything while not invincible, I can rack up a good star-kill combo here.
